<p>Debian GNU/kFreeBSD is a port that consists of
<a href="http://www.gnu.org/">GNU userland</a> using the
<a href="http://www.gnu.org/software/libc/">GNU C library</a> on top of
<a href="https://www.freebsd.org/">FreeBSD</a>'s kernel, coupled with the
regular <a href="https://packages.debian.org/">Debian package set</a>.</p>

<div class="important">
<p>This is a release in progress.  It has been released with Debian 6.0 (Squeeze)
as a technology preview and the first non-Linux port.</p>
</div>

